For reference to the study below, the XRD patterns of graphite reveal at least four distinctive reflections (see Fig.2
                        ): (002), (010), (004), and (110) at 2θ = 26.4°, 42.5°, 54.6°, and 77.5°, respectively. The (002) and (004) peaks indicate the interlayer spacing and stacking of graphene sheets, with d
                        (002) = 3.35 Å In contrast, the (010) and (110) peaks are associated with the in-plane spacing between carbon atoms and their arrangement within the graphene layers. The 2θ values of these graphite peaks are key indicators for the structural characterization of carbon-based materials.
